Before submitting your Service Request, make sure you confirm;
•IMEI and Model of device matches the one you will be sending
back to Samsung
•Delivery details (name and address) match where the
replacement device will be sent

Next to each IMEI you will be able to view;
•Enrolment end-date (when your subscription expires)
•Program Term (duration of subscription)
•Program Allowance (Swap Allowance)
•SR Complete (history of how many SRs have been completed for
this IMEI)

Cancel Swap Request Confirmation To cancel a Swap Request,
Click, CANCEL on the
bottom right-hand corner
and click, YES to confirm
**Once cancelled you will
not be able to retrieve this
SR

Asurion_Public
Resume or Cancel an Open Swap Request
The administrator can
resume or cancel a pending
Swap Request when logging
back into the portal and
selecting “Resume/Cancel
Open Service Request” tab
on the left options bar
**If you have an open SR
for an IMEI you will not be
able to start a new SR
1
1
Asurion_Public
Manage MyAccount Features
The administrator can select,
Manage MyAccount to view
Swap Request History
including;
•Date shipped
•Tracking no. details
•Proof of swap for IMEI
update verification
